*[[Daphne de Beistegui]] portrays Lily Potter in {{DH|F2}}.
*Lily is portrayed by British actresses [[Christiana Hutchings]], [[Zoe Brough]], and [[Cristina Fray]] alternating the role in {{CC|P1}}.<ref>[http://www.snitchseeker.com/harry-potter-news/cursed-child-new-feature-reveals-first-look-at-harry-ron-and-hermione-together-104610/ 'Cursed Child' new feature reveals first look at Harry, Ron & Hermione together.] ''SnitchSeeker.'' 13 July 2016. Retrieved 26 July 2016.</ref><ref>Rowling, J.K., Tiffany, John and Thorne, Jack. ''Harry Potter and the Cursed Child: Parts One and Two.'' Broadway, New York, NY: Arhur A. Levine Books, 2016. Print. pp. 313-15.</ref>
*Lily was the first of Harry's children to be introduced in the epilogue, where she was shown holding her father's hand, much as her [[Ginevra Weasley|mother]] was introduced in ''[[Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone|Philosopher's Stone]]''.
*She is the only child of [[Harry Potter|Harry]] and Ginny who was named after a person still living at the end of the series: [[Luna Lovegood|Luna]] still lived while [[Lily Potter (I)|Lily]], [[James Potter (I)|James]], [[Sirius Black|Sirius]], [[Albus Dumbledore|Albus]], and [[Severus Snape|Severus]] all had died.
*In the film version, Lily is seen standing with James, even sitting on top of his trunk when he was taking it into King's Cross.
*In the novel, Lily protests about her desire to go to Hogwarts, despite not being able to go for another two years. This is very similar to the desire her mother, Ginny, expressed in ''[[Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone|Philosopher's Stone]].''
*She is related to the [[House of Black]] because her maternal great-grandmother was [[Cedrella Black]]. Her maternal great-grandaunt was [[Lucretia Black]]. Some sort of relative on her paternal side was [[Dorea Black]].
*She is also related to [[Tom Riddle|Lord Voldemort]] and the Gaunts through her paternal ancestor [[Ignotus Peverell]]. Ignotus Peverell's brother was [[Cadmus Peverell]] who is Voldemort's ancestor.
*Apparently Lily inherited her impatient and enthusiastic traits from Ginny, because when Harry and Ron were going on the [[Hogwarts Express]], Ginny asked her mother, Molly, if she could go, much like Lily told her father Harry that she wanted to go when Albus and James were going.

